Financial risk management

Financial risk factors

The Group’s activities expose it to market risk (including currency risk, interest rate risk and price risk), credit

risk and liquidity risk, The Group’s overall risk management strategy seeks to minimise adverse effects from the unpredictability of financial markets on the Group’s financial performance, The Group uses financial instruments such as currency forwards and foreign currency borrowings to manage certain financial risk exposures.
